    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="228"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1743</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.09 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3035. Following received from Foreign Office, dated October 16:<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d228fn1">A notification to the same effect on the part of his
                        Government was addressed by the French Ambassador to the Secretary of State
                        October 18 (File No. 763.72112/1762).</note>
                </p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>The Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs presents his compliments to the
                        United States Ambassador and has the honor to state that the vice admiral
                        commanding the eastern Mediterranean squadron of the Allied fleets has
                        declared a blockade of the Bulgarian coast in the Aegean Sea commencing from
                        6 a. m. on the 16th instant. Forty-eight hours’ grace from the moment of the
                        commencement of the blockade has been assigned for the departure of neutral
                        vessels from the blockaded area.</p>
                    <p>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir E. Grey</persName> requests that the above
                        may be brought to the knowledge of the United States Government.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
